sentence: Wall Street's main indexes jumped on Wednesday, with the S&P 500 crawling towards a record high in a broad rally led by tech stocks, although some investors were cautious following a stalemate over the new coronavirus relief bill.

.N

At 10:29 ET, the Dow Jones Industrial Average .DJI was up 0.90% at 27,937.07.
The S&P 500 .SPX was up 1.10% at 3,370.46 and the Nasdaq Composite .IXIC was up 1.82% at 10,979.554.
